Granollers Defeats Verdasco in Three Sets to Win Tennis’s Swiss Open

-- B y   P e t e r - J o s e p h   H e g a r t y
-- 
2011-07-31T16:41:31Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-31/granollers-defeats-verdasco-in-three-sets-to-win-tennis-s-swiss-open.html
Spain ’s Marcel Granollers beat his
compatriot  Fernando Verdasco  in three sets to win the final of
tennis’s Swiss Open in Gstaad today.  Granollers won 6-4, 3-6, 6-3 for a top prize of 72,600
euros ($104,000). It was his second career title.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
 Christopher Elser  at   celser@bloomberg.net . 